cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper deals with the design of neuromorphic systems using memristive crossbar arrays and proposes a framework for transforming deep neural networks to enable their efficient realization on such systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of clustering techniques and optimization algorithms, which are relevant to the categories cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). The paper also discusses the use of network pruning and its limitations, which falls under the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed framework on image classification tasks, which is relevant to the category cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
